          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Job 32:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Ram) and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 22:21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Aram).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Chelubai.—Strictly, the Chelubite or Calebite, a gentilic term formed from Caleb (1Chronicles 2:18). This seems to show that we are concerned here not so much with individual sons of Hezron as with families or clans of Hezronites.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Chelubai.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Strictly, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the Chelubite",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " or ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Calebite,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " a gentilic term formed from Caleb (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 2:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). This seems to show that we are concerned here not so much with individual sons of Hezron as with families or clans of Hezronites.",
            "children": []
